      <div xml:id="Aink3">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> pālpala vūṟuka pakaṭupala ciṟakka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> vittiya vuḻavar nelloṭu peyarum</l>
          <l> pūkkaña lūraṉ ṟaṉmaṉai </l>
          <l> vāḻkkai polika veṉavēṭ ṭēmē. </l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May many [drops of] milk trickle! May many bulls grow!' </l>
<l>          That's what our mother wants. As for us: </l>
<l>          '[There is] a man from a land teeming with flowers,</l>
<l>          where ploughmen, after sowing, return with paddy:</l>
<l>          May the livelihood of his household flourish!' — that's what we want. </l>
          


        </lg>
      </div>
